Can you elaborate on the various physical and biological factors that influence the habitat of an organism? Additionally, could you provide two detailed examples of habitats, one in a tropical region and one in a polar region, including the species that inhabit them? 
[C++ code]
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
int main() {
  // Definition of habitat
  cout << "A habitat is the natural environment in which an organism lives and thrives, characterized by various physical and biological factors such as climate, soil, vegetation, and other living organisms.\n\n";
  // Examples of habitats
  cout << "Two detailed examples of habitats are:\n";
  cout << "- Tropical habitat: The Amazon Rainforest, which is home to numerous species such as jaguars, monkeys, and toucans, as well as unique plant life such as the giant water lily.\n";
  cout << "- Polar habitat: The Arctic Tundra, which is characterized by a harsh climate and permafrost, and is home to species such as polar bears, arctic foxes, and reindeer.\n";
  return 0;
}
